Australia won the toss and chose to bat in the opening Chappell-Hadlee Trophy one-day international against New Zealand in Sydney on Sunday.The top-ranked Australians, who lost their last ODI series 5-0 in South Africa in October, left out all-rounders Glenn Maxwell and James Faulkner.The Black Caps, ranked third, will give fast bowler Lockie Ferguson his ODI debut and left out paceman Tim Southee.Australia: David Warner, Aaron Finch, Steve Smith (capt), George Bailey, Mitchell Marsh, Travis Head, Matthew Wade, Mitchell Starc, Pat Cummins, Adam Zampa, Josh Hazlewood.New Zealand: Martin Guptill, Tom Latham, Kane Williamson (capt), Jimmy Neesham, Colin Munro, BJ Watling, Mitchell Santner, Colin de Grandhomme, Matt Henry, Lockie Ferguson, Trent Boult.Umpires: Kumar Dharmasena (SRI) and Mick Martell (AUS)Third umpire: Paul Wilson (AUS)Match referee: Richie Richardson (WIS)-AFP